<p>I can successfully install laravel 5 on windows like that :</p>  <ul> <li>with cmd or cygwin : <code>composer global require "laravel/installer=~1.1"</code>, then <code>laravel new myproject</code></li> <li>with cmd : <code>composer create-project laravel/laravel myproject --prefer-dist</code></li> </ul>  <p>But if I use <code>composer create-project</code> with cygwin, it is not working. For example, if I do <code>php artisan</code>, I get this : </p>  <pre><code>PHP Warning:  require(/cygdrive/c/xampp/htdocs/phpacademy/l5pa2/bootstrap/../vendor/autoload.php): failed to open stream: No such file or directory in /cygdrive/c/xampp/htdocs/phpacademy/l5pa2/bootstrap/autoload.php on line 17 PHP Fatal error:  require(): Failed opening required '/cygdrive/c/xampp/htdocs/phpacademy/l5pa2/bootstrap/../vendor/autoload.php' (include_path='.:/usr/share/pear:/usr/share/php/php') in /cygdrive/c/xampp/htdocs/phpacademy/l5pa2/bootstrap/autoload.php on line 17 </code></pre>  <p>Comparing with the working installations, I found that those files are missing on the non-working cygwin installation : </p>  <ul> <li>\myproject\vendor\autoload.php</li> <li>\myproject\vendor\composer\autoload_classmap.php</li> <li>\myproject\vendor\composer\autoload_files.php</li> <li>\myproject\vendor\composer\autoload_namespaces.php</li> <li>\myproject\vendor\composer\autoload_psr4.php   </li> <li>\myproject\vendor\composer\autoload_real.php</li> <li>\myproject\vendor\composer\ClassLoader.php</li> <li>\myproject\vendor\composer\LICENSE</li> </ul>  <p>Under the non-working cygwin installation, there's only "installed.json" in \myproject\vendor\composer. If I copy the missing files there, I can then do <code>php artisan</code>.</p>  <p>So the question is, why <code>composer create-project</code> with cygwin doesn't install those files ?</p>